This paper is about using machine learning techniques to enable a robot to learn complex motion sequences. The paper specifically mentions real robot experiments, indicating that it is focused on robotics (cs.RO). The use of recurrent neural networks and sequence learning techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on enabling the robot to accomplish complex behaviors from high-level instructions suggests that it may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
